---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import CommandPaletteWrapper from '../components/CommandPaletteWrapper.astro';
import SideNav from '../components/SideNav.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Editorial Manual | alumi news"
  description="How we use AI models, human oversight, and editorial standards to produce health content that respects the reader."
>
  <Header slot="header" />

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="manual-hero">
    <div class="container-editorial">
      <div class="max-w-narrow">
        <div class="manual-kicker">
          <span class="kicker-line"></span>
          <span>Internal Document</span>
        </div>
        <h1 class="font-serif text-display-2 font-semibold mt-5 mb-5 leading-tight">
          The alumi<br/>
          <span class="italic font-normal text-primary-600">Editorial Manual</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="font-body text-body-lg text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400 max-w-lg">
          How we use AI models, human oversight, and editorial standards to produce health content that respects the reader's intelligence.
        </p>
        <div class="manual-meta">
          <span>Last updated: March 2026</span>
          <span>Version 1.0</span>
          <span>For all contributors</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- TOC -->
  <section class="manual-toc">
    <div class="container-editorial">
      <div class="max-w-narrow">
        <div class="toc-label">Contents</div>
        <div class="toc-grid">
          <a class="toc-item" href="#mission"><span class="toc-num">01</span> Mission</a>
          <a class="toc-item" href="#voice"><span class="toc-num">02</span> Voice & tone</a>
          <a class="toc-item" href="#evidence"><span class="toc-num">03</span> Evidence standards</a>
          <a class="toc-item" href="#pipeline"><span class="toc-num">04</span> The pipeline</a>
          <a class="toc-item" href="#structure"><span class="toc-num">05</span> Article structure</a>
          <a class="toc-item" href="#rules"><span class="toc-num">06</span> Always / Never</a>
          <a class="toc-item" href="#legitimacy"><span class="toc-num">07</span> Legitimacy</a>
          <a class="toc-item" href="#funnel"><span class="toc-num">08</span> The funnel</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Content -->
  <div class="container-editorial">
    <div class="max-w-narrow manual-content">

      <!-- 01 MISSION -->
      <section class="manual-section" id="mission">
        <div class="manual-kicker"><span class="kicker-line"></span><span>01 &mdash; Mission</span></div>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-heading-1 font-semibold mt-4 mb-6">What we are here to do</h2>
        <p class="dropcap">We are health obsessives who got tired of the math. Ninety percent of what's written about health online is agenda-driven &mdash; funded by the industries it should be scrutinizing, or quackery dressed as rebellion, or clickbait wearing a lab coat. We built alumi to push back.</p>
        <p>AI models handle research, editorial judgment, and quality control. A human writes &mdash; sometimes solo, sometimes with Opus as a collaborator. The result is seriously balanced coverage of every subject we touch &mdash; institutionally skeptical, honest about what we don't know, and built for people who want real information instead of managed uncertainty.</p>

        <div class="manual-pullquote">
          <p>"The reader should finish each piece feeling accurately informed and respected &mdash; never lectured, never frightened without cause."</p>
        </div>

        <p>We are not doctors. We are not journalists. We are obsessive readers who got fed up and decided to do it properly. Editorial independence is not a principle we hold despite the business model. It is the mechanism by which the business model works.</p>
      </section>

      <!-- 02 VOICE -->
      <section class="manual-section" id="voice">
        <div class="manual-kicker"><span class="kicker-line"></span><span>02 &mdash; Voice & tone</span></div>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-heading-1 font-semibold mt-4 mb-6">How we sound</h2>
        <p>The alumi voice is built from four archetypes. Misread any one and the prose tips into parody.</p>

        <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-semibold italic mt-8 mb-3">The Prosecutor &mdash; forensic structure</h3>
        <p>Premises stack until conclusions feel inevitable. Wit that works, never decorates. Never use cleverness as a substitute for evidence, and never use evidence as a substitute for a point of view.</p>

        <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-semibold italic mt-8 mb-3">The Documentarian &mdash; rhythmic economy</h3>
        <p>Varied sentence length controls pace. Cold opens &mdash; start inside the story, not outside it. The camera doesn't explain what you're looking at; it trusts you to see it.</p>

        <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-semibold italic mt-8 mb-3">The Cartographer &mdash; no throat-clearing</h3>
        <p>Start on the claim. Complexity is dissolved, not displayed. If you need a setup sentence to explain your opening, rewrite the opening. Intelligence is assumed; expertise is not.</p>

        <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-semibold italic mt-8 mb-3">The Comedian &mdash; zero patience for the gap</h3>
        <p>Not an insider &mdash; but built to hold insiders accountable. No tolerance for the distance between what's officially claimed and what the evidence actually shows. The joke is the argument. Name the gap.</p>

        <div class="manual-callout">
          <div class="manual-callout-label">Tone test</div>
          <p>Read your lede aloud. If it sounds like a press release, a Wikipedia article, or a wellness podcast intro &mdash; rewrite it. If it sounds like something a smart, slightly impatient friend would say at a dinner party &mdash; you're close.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- 03 EVIDENCE -->
      <section class="manual-section" id="evidence">
        <div class="manual-kicker"><span class="kicker-line"></span><span>03 &mdash; Evidence standards</span></div>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-heading-1 font-semibold mt-4 mb-6">What counts as evidence</h2>
        <p>Not all research is equal. Treating it as such is the fastest way to erode reader trust.</p>

        <ol class="evidence-list">
          <li><span class="ev-marker">&bull;</span><span><strong>Cochrane systematic reviews</strong> are the gold standard. Treat them accordingly.</span></li>
          <li><span class="ev-marker">&bull;</span><span><strong>RCTs</strong> are strong when well-designed, adequately powered, and independently funded. Check all three.</span></li>
          <li><span class="ev-marker">&bull;</span><span><strong>Observational studies</strong> establish correlation, not causation. Say this in prose, not in a footnote.</span></li>
          <li><span class="ev-marker">&bull;</span><span><strong>In vitro and animal studies</strong> are preliminary signal. One mouse study &ne; a Cochrane review.</span></li>
          <li><span class="ev-marker">&bull;</span><span><strong>Industry-funded research</strong> is not automatically invalid &mdash; but the funding source must be disclosed and the methodology scrutinized harder.</span></li>
          <li><span class="ev-marker">&bull;</span><span><strong>Expert opinion</strong> is context, not evidence. Name the expert, name their conflicts.</span></li>
        </ol>

        <div class="manual-pullquote">
          <p>"When evidence is mixed or preliminary, say so in the prose &mdash; don't bury it in a closing caveat."</p>
        </div>

        <p>A closing "consult your doctor" does not undo three paragraphs of overstatement. If the evidence doesn't support a strong conclusion, the piece should not have one.</p>
      </section>

      <!-- 04 PIPELINE -->
      <section class="manual-section" id="pipeline">
        <div class="manual-kicker"><span class="kicker-line"></span><span>04 &mdash; The pipeline</span></div>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-heading-1 font-semibold mt-4 mb-6">How an article gets made</h2>
        <p>Eight stages. AI handles discovery, research, and quality control. A human writes. This is not a cost-cutting measure &mdash; it is a quality architecture.</p>

        <div class="pipeline">
          <div class="pipe-step">
            <div class="pipe-num">1</div>
            <div class="pipe-body">
              <div class="pipe-title">Topic discovery</div>
              <p class="pipe-desc">Three daily scouts surface emerging research, breaking health news, and underserved subject areas. Topics are ranked by editorial priority and queued.</p>
              <span class="pipe-model">Gemini 2.5 Pro + Google Search &middot; 3&times;/day</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="pipe-step">
            <div class="pipe-num">2</div>
            <div class="pipe-body">
              <div class="pipe-title">Deep research</div>
              <p class="pipe-desc">Full literature review for the queued topic. Primary sources, methodology assessment, conflicting studies, funding sources.</p>
              <span class="pipe-model">Gemini 2.5 Pro + Google Search &middot; fallback: Sonnet</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="pipe-step">
            <div class="pipe-num">3</div>
            <div class="pipe-body">
              <div class="pipe-title">Editorial brief</div>
              <p class="pipe-desc">Assigns archetype, tone preset, structural density, and pacing. Manually queued topics receive mandatory editorial direction.</p>
              <span class="pipe-model">Gemini Flash &middot; fallback: Sonnet</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="pipe-step pipe-step-human">
            <div class="pipe-num pipe-num-human">4</div>
            <div class="pipe-body">
              <div class="pipe-title">Human writing</div>
              <p class="pipe-desc">The pipeline pauses here. A human takes the research brief and writes the article &mdash; sometimes from scratch, sometimes with Claude Opus as a writing partner. About half the prose is human, half AI-assisted. This is the only stage that cannot be automated &mdash; and it is the point of the entire system.</p>
              <span class="pipe-model">Human + Claude Opus &middot; non-negotiable pause</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="pipe-step">
            <div class="pipe-num">5</div>
            <div class="pipe-body">
              <div class="pipe-title">Independence review</div>
              <p class="pipe-desc">Adversarial review. Checks for overstatement, missing caveats, unverified claims. Cross-references against PubMed. Applies corrections.</p>
              <span class="pipe-model">Grok 3 + PubMed verification + Flash corrections</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="pipe-step">
            <div class="pipe-num">6</div>
            <div class="pipe-body">
              <div class="pipe-title">Quality control</div>
              <p class="pipe-desc">Final editorial gate: publish, revise, or kill. Mechanical voice audit checks for prohibited constructions, throat-clearing, and tone drift.</p>
              <span class="pipe-model">Gemini Flash &middot; fallback: Sonnet</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="pipe-step">
            <div class="pipe-num">7</div>
            <div class="pipe-body">
              <div class="pipe-title">Voice rewrite (if triggered)</div>
              <p class="pipe-desc">Triggered by QC when voice drift is detected. Prose-only rewrite &mdash; facts and structure are not changed. Skipped for human-written articles that pass QC clean.</p>
              <span class="pipe-model">Sonnet &rarr; Gemini &rarr; Grok &middot; cascade</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="pipe-step">
            <div class="pipe-num">8</div>
            <div class="pipe-body">
              <div class="pipe-title">Publish</div>
              <p class="pipe-desc">GitHub commit, Vercel deploy, AI-generated editorial illustration, featured rotation. Article is live.</p>
              <span class="pipe-model">Automated &middot; ~$0.13/article all-in</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- 05 STRUCTURE -->
      <section class="manual-section" id="structure">
        <div class="manual-kicker"><span class="kicker-line"></span><span>05 &mdash; Article structure</span></div>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-heading-1 font-semibold mt-4 mb-6">How a piece is built</h2>

        <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-semibold italic mt-8 mb-3">The lede</h3>
        <p>Start inside the story. A number, a scene, a contradiction, a document. The reader should know within two sentences what they are reading and why it matters.</p>

        <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-semibold italic mt-8 mb-3">The structure</h3>
        <p>Each section earns the next. Don't announce what you're about to say &mdash; say it. Subheadings make claims, not labels. "The funding problem" is a label. "The researchers were paid by the companies they were studying" is a claim.</p>

        <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-semibold italic mt-8 mb-3">The close</h3>
        <p>Don't recap. Don't soften. End where the argument ends &mdash; on the finding, the implication, or the unanswered question the reader now has the tools to consider.</p>

        <div class="manual-callout">
          <div class="manual-callout-label">Scene over assertion</div>
          <p>State the finding once &mdash; then show what it looks like in a person's life, an institution's behavior, or a document's language. The reader should reach the conclusion, not be handed it.</p>
        </div>

        <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-semibold italic mt-8 mb-3">Sources</h3>
        <p>Every claim needs a source. Every source needs a date. Industry funding is disclosed in prose, not citations. If you cannot source a claim, the claim comes out.</p>
      </section>

      <!-- 06 RULES -->
      <section class="manual-section" id="rules">
        <div class="manual-kicker"><span class="kicker-line"></span><span>06 &mdash; Always / Never</span></div>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-heading-1 font-semibold mt-4 mb-6">The non-negotiables</h2>

        <div class="rules-grid">
          <div class="rules-col">
            <div class="rules-col-label rules-always">Always</div>
            <ul class="rules-list">
              <li>Oxford comma, US English</li>
              <li>Start on the claim &mdash; no setup sentences</li>
              <li>Name the awkward thing first</li>
              <li>Say when evidence is mixed or preliminary &mdash; in the prose</li>
              <li>Assume intelligence, not expertise</li>
              <li>Edge targets institutions and bad ideas, not patients making real decisions</li>
              <li>Disclose funding sources for cited research</li>
              <li>Let the scene argue &mdash; state the finding once, then show it</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="rules-col">
            <div class="rules-col-label rules-never">Never</div>
            <ul class="rules-list">
              <li>"This isn't X, it's Y" constructions</li>
              <li>Hallmark-card warmth</li>
              <li>Breathless wellness hype</li>
              <li>Reflexive contrarianism</li>
              <li>One mouse study presented as settled science</li>
              <li>A closing disclaimer that undoes the body of the piece</li>
              <li>Subheadings that label rather than claim</li>
              <li>Setup sentences before the lede</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- 07 LEGITIMACY -->
      <section class="manual-section" id="legitimacy">
        <div class="manual-kicker"><span class="kicker-line"></span><span>07 &mdash; Legitimacy</span></div>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-heading-1 font-semibold mt-4 mb-6">How we justify publishing health content</h2>
        <p>Fair question. We are not physicians, and we are not journalists. We are health nerds with a rigorous process &mdash; and that process is the entire point. Primary sources checked, methodology examined, conflicting evidence included, funding disclosed. The pipeline enforces it. The independence review catches what slips through.</p>
        <p>Most health content fails not because the writers lack credentials but because the incentives are wrong. Industry pays for favorable conclusions. Wellness influencers sell certainty. We have no sponsors, no sacred cows, and no financial interest in any outcome except getting it right.</p>

        <div class="manual-pullquote">
          <p>"We do not diagnose. We do not recommend treatments. We explain what the evidence shows &mdash; and we are explicit when the evidence is weak, contested, or absent."</p>
        </div>

        <p>Every piece ends with a disclaimer because the disclaimer is true &mdash; not because it provides legal cover for irresponsible claims in the body of the text.</p>
      </section>

      <!-- 08 FUNNEL -->
      <section class="manual-section" id="funnel">
        <div class="manual-kicker"><span class="kicker-line"></span><span>08 &mdash; The funnel</span></div>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-heading-1 font-semibold mt-4 mb-6">How the magazine connects to the app</h2>
        <p>The sequence is fixed: <strong>value &mdash; trust &mdash; download.</strong> A reader who downloads the app because an article earned their trust is worth ten who clicked a banner.</p>

        <div class="manual-callout">
          <div class="manual-callout-label">The rule</div>
          <p>The moment the magazine feels like an ad for the app, the trust that makes the recommendation work evaporates.</p>
        </div>

        <p>Article CTAs are contextual, not generic. An article about ferritin links to biomarker tracking, not the homepage. The reader should experience the CTA as a continuation of the article, not a commercial interruption.</p>
      </section>

      <!-- Disclaimer -->
      <div class="manual-disclaimer">
        <p><strong>Editorial use only.</strong> This document is an internal manual for alumi contributors, editors, and AI pipeline configuration. It does not constitute medical advice. alumi Health content is for informational purposes only and does not constitute medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment.</p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Footer -->
  <div class="manual-footer">
    <p><em>alumi news</em> &mdash; Evidence. Wherever it leads. &middot; Internal document, March 2026</p>
  </div>

  <Footer slot="footer" />
  <CommandPaletteWrapper />
  <SideNav />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .manual-hero {
    @apply pt-32 md:pt-36 pb-12 md:pb-16;
    @apply border-b border-stone-200 dark:border-stone-800;
  }

  .manual-kicker {
    @apply flex items-center gap-3;
    @apply text-overline font-semibold text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400;
  }

  .kicker-line {
    @apply block w-6 h-px bg-primary-600 dark:bg-primary-400;
  }

  .manual-meta {
    @apply flex flex-wrap gap-6 mt-8;
    @apply text-xs text-stone-400 dark:text-stone-500 font-sans;
  }

  /* TOC */
  .manual-toc {
    @apply py-10 border-b border-stone-200 dark:border-stone-800;
  }

  .toc-label {
    @apply text-overline font-semibold text-stone-400 dark:text-stone-500 mb-5;
  }

  .toc-grid {
    @apply grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-4 gap-2;
  }

  .toc-item {
    @apply flex items-center gap-2.5 py-2;
    @apply text-sm text-stone-500 dark:text-stone-400 no-underline;
    @apply border-b border-stone-200/50 dark:border-stone-800/50;
    @apply hover:text-primary-600 dark:hover:text-primary-400 transition-colors;
  }

  .toc-num {
    @apply text-[10px] text-stone-400 dark:text-stone-600 font-mono;
    min-width: 18px;
  }

  /* Content */
  .manual-content {
    @apply pb-16;
  }

  .manual-section {
    @apply py-14 border-b border-stone-200 dark:border-stone-800;
  }

  .manual-section:last-of-type {
    @apply border-b-0;
  }

  .manual-content p {
    @apply font-body text-body text-stone-700 dark:text-stone-300 mb-5;
  }

  .manual-content p:last-child {
    @apply mb-0;
  }

  .manual-content strong {
    @apply font-medium;
  }

  .manual-content em {
    @apply italic;
  }

  /* Drop cap */
  .dropcap::first-letter {
    @apply font-serif text-primary-600 font-bold;
    font-size: 4.5rem;
    line-height: 0.8;
    float: left;
    margin: 0.05em 0.12em 0 0;
  }

  /* Pull quote */
  .manual-pullquote {
    @apply my-10 py-6 pl-7 border-l-[3px] border-primary-600;
  }

  .manual-pullquote p {
    @apply font-serif text-xl italic text-stone-500 dark:text-stone-400 leading-relaxed mb-0;
  }

  /* Callout */
  .manual-callout {
    @apply my-8 p-6 rounded-lg;
    @apply bg-stone-100 dark:bg-stone-800/50;
    @apply border-l-[3px] border-primary-600;
  }

  .manual-callout-label {
    @apply text-overline font-semibold text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400 mb-2;
  }

  .manual-callout p {
    @apply text-sm text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400 leading-relaxed mb-0;
  }

  /* Evidence list */
  .evidence-list {
    @apply list-none my-5;
  }

  .evidence-list li {
    @apply flex gap-3 py-3;
    @apply border-b border-stone-200/50 dark:border-stone-800/50;
    @apply text-sm text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400 leading-relaxed;
  }

  .evidence-list li:last-child {
    @apply border-b-0;
  }

  .ev-marker {
    @apply text-primary-600 text-xs flex-shrink-0 pt-0.5;
  }

  /* Pipeline */
  .pipeline {
    @apply my-8 flex flex-col;
  }

  .pipe-step {
    @apply flex gap-5 py-4;
    @apply border-b border-stone-200/50 dark:border-stone-800/50;
  }

  .pipe-step:last-child {
    @apply border-b-0;
  }

  .pipe-num {
    @apply w-6 h-6 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5;
    @apply bg-stone-400 dark:bg-stone-600 text-white dark:text-stone-200;
    @apply text-[11px] font-semibold font-sans;
  }

  .pipe-num-human {
    @apply bg-primary-600 dark:bg-primary-500;
  }

  .pipe-body {
    @apply flex-1;
  }

  .pipe-title {
    @apply text-sm font-semibold font-sans text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-100 mb-1;
  }

  .pipe-desc {
    @apply text-sm text-stone-500 dark:text-stone-400 leading-relaxed mb-0;
  }

  .pipe-model {
    @apply inline-block mt-2 px-2.5 py-0.5 rounded-full;
    @apply text-[10px] font-sans font-medium;
    @apply text-stone-400 dark:text-stone-500;
    @apply bg-stone-100 dark:bg-stone-800;
  }

  /* Rules grid */
  .rules-grid {
    @apply grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-6;
  }

  .rules-col {
    @apply bg-stone-100 dark:bg-stone-800/50 rounded-lg p-5;
  }

  .rules-col-label {
    @apply text-overline font-semibold mb-3;
  }

  .rules-always {
    @apply text-green-600 dark:text-green-400;
  }

  .rules-never {
    @apply text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400;
  }

  .rules-list {
    @apply list-none;
  }

  .rules-list li {
    @apply py-1.5 text-sm text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400 leading-relaxed;
    @apply border-b border-stone-200/50 dark:border-stone-700/50;
    @apply flex gap-2;
  }

  .rules-list li:last-child {
    @apply border-b-0;
  }

  .rules-list li::before {
    content: '\2013';
    @apply text-stone-400 dark:text-stone-600 flex-shrink-0;
  }

  /* Disclaimer */
  .manual-disclaimer {
    @apply mt-16 p-5 rounded-lg;
    @apply bg-stone-100 dark:bg-stone-800/50;
    @apply border-l-[3px] border-primary-600;
  }

  .manual-disclaimer p {
    @apply text-xs text-stone-500 dark:text-stone-400 leading-relaxed font-sans mb-0;
  }

  /* Footer */
  .manual-footer {
    @apply py-8 text-center;
    @apply border-t border-stone-200 dark:border-stone-800;
  }

  .manual-footer p {
    @apply text-xs text-stone-400 dark:text-stone-500 font-sans;
  }

  .manual-footer em {
    @apply font-serif italic text-stone-500 dark:text-stone-400 not-italic;
  }
</style>
